lead_paragraph: Appeals judges at a special court in The Hague quashed the conviction of a Lebanese journalist who was accused of exposing witnesses in the trial of the alleged assassins of former Lebanese prime minister Rafik al-Hariri.

headline.main: Lebanese Journalist Acquitted of Contempt of Hague Court on Appeal
